Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Senior Full Stack Engineer* role with *Piper Companies*. I bring over three years of professional experience building scalable full stack web applications, REST APIs, and AI-powered backend services, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade full stack systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands — designing scalable REST APIs, building responsive ReactJS front-ends, and maintaining reliable backend services using Node.js, Java, and relational databases. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and implemented a scalable REST API layer using Node.js and TypeScript that routes natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and ownership of end-to-end delivery. I optimized REST API routing and agent concurrency to reduce end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50% through targeted performance optimization, and architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system with unit testing evaluation hooks via LangSmith for tracing, debugging, and quality tracking across distributed full stack workflows. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to an Identity & Access Management web application using ReactJS, TypeScript, Spring Boot, and AWS in an Agile environment, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with scalable backend services and responsive UI development. I also designed a cloud-agnostic REST API Storage Service using Java, PostgreSQL (SQL relational database), and Redis handling file operations across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO — and developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions and AWS Lambda to handle long-running data import jobs, applying performance optimization and troubleshooting to prevent production timeouts. Together, these roles have prepared me to take full ownership of assigned features, collaborate effectively with product and business stakeholders, and contribute to long-term platform architecture and strategy.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, GPU-accelerated computing, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster, managing the full model lifecycle from training to CI/CD-style deployment. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming and AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph for 50+ students — designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly for both technical and non-technical audiences, directly mirroring the communication skills and cross-functional collaboration this role values. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to Piper Companies and its clients.


I have always been passionate about delivering measurable value through specialization and exceptional service, and the relentless pursuit of the common goal through discipline, perseverance, and teamwork — and I envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of Piper Companies' mission to become the primary provider of talent by earning maximum customer share within the services they deliver. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

